wiki.summary: Gunna spreads a motivational message on “DO BETTER”, one of the long-awaited songs from WUNNA. On the song, the Atlanta rapper encourages the listener to stay focused to earn success and money while drawing a parallel with his own come-up, in a similar fashion to his 2016 song “Don’t Give Up”. This track was teased numerous times by Gunna since summer 2019, raising hype around its release. The track title was confirmed on Instagram Live on April 23, 2020. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Gunna spreads a motivational message on “DO BETTER”, one of the long-awaited songs from WUNNA. On the song, the Atlanta rapper encourages the listener to stay focused to earn success and money while drawing a parallel with his own come-up, in a similar fashion to his 2016 song “Don’t Give Up”. This track was teased numerous times by Gunna since summer 2019, raising hype around its release. The track title was confirmed on Instagram Live on April 23, 2020. In a May 2020 interview with Highsnobiety, Gunna said: “DO BETTER” came from an experience. I was in LA and I was taking out this girl I talked to. I was just really trying to speak to her, telling her how I want to see her do better. Read more on Last.fm.
